              Training for Grads &amp; Staff
             </a>
             <a href="../undergraduates/academic-certificate-courses.html" title="Learn more about the Undergraduate Leadership Certificate">
              <br/>
              Certificate Program for Undergrads
              <br/>
             </a>
             <a href="../phd-students/fellowship-in-leadership.html" title="Learn more about the Fellowship in Leadership">
              Fellowship in Leadership for Grads &amp; Staff
             </a>
            </p>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="panel" href="#collapse9" target="self">
        <div aria-expanded="false" class="panel-heading" id="panel9">
         <h4 class="panel-title">
          <span class="plus_sym">
           <img height="20" src="../images/structure/plus.svg" width="20"/>
          </span>
          Build a network of trusted advisors
         </h4>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-collapse collapse" id="collapse9">
         <div class="panel-body top_body">
          <div>
           <p>
            Having a good team is vital, but sometimes it’s not enough. Many new challenges require expertise beyond your collective skills.
           </p>
           <p>
            When you develop a set of trusted advisors, you will:
           </p>
           <ul>
            <li>
             Benefit from the specialized knowledge of others.
            </li>
            <li>
             Be prepared to act quickly when faced with new problems.
            </li>
            <li>
             Create mutual trust that benefits you and your peers.
            </li>
           </ul>
          </div>
         </div>
         <div class="panel-body bottom_body">
          <div>
           <p>
            At the Center for Leadership, you will begin building your own network of trusted advisors.
           </p>
           <a class="button learn-more">
            Learn More
           </a>
           <div class="learn-content">
            <p>
             <a href="../undergraduates/coaching.html" title="Learn more about Coaching for Undergrads">
              Coaching for Undergrads
             </a>
